William T. HUTCHENS, Petitioner-Appellant, v. STATE OF ALABAMA, Respondent-Appellee. No. 30662

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 24, 1971. William T. Hutchens, pro se; Michael Simonetti, Birmingham, Ala., for petitioner-appellant. MacDonald Gallion, Atty. Gen., Richard E. Calhoun, Asst. Atty. Gen., Montgomery, Ala., for respondent-appellee.

Before BROWN, Chief Judge, INGRA-HAM and RONEY, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir. See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5th Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5th Cir., 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
